From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 16:40:13 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] n2: lib-only de-workspace + in-process brush executor hook

Re-applies sarun's delta over the pristine n2 base:
  * Cargo.toml: de-workspace to a standalone lib-only crate (drop [[bin]],
    benches, jemalloc/windows deps; empty default feature; add [lib]).
  * lib.rs: pub graph/process/signal; drop jemalloc global_allocator and the
    process_win mod (unix-only fork).
  * process.rs: a global in-process Executor hook (set_executor/executor).
  * process_posix.rs: run_command routes to the executor when installed,
    never posix_spawning /bin/sh.
  * signal.rs: register_sigint is a no-op when the executor is active.
  * run.rs: force -j1 under the executor; add run_state() for an already-loaded
    in-memory State.
  * load.rs: read_from_content / read_from_content_with_db build a State from
    in-memory ninja with a memfd (or disk) db, no build.ninja/.n2_db temp.
  * db.rs: Writer::in_memory() (memfd-backed empty db).
  * densemap.rs: len()/iter() to walk the build graph for provenance.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01XyA6FzC6QGgsrjEYEBJV46
